p:
In response to cellular stress, HSF1 and HSF2 TFs activate genes encoding heat shock proteins (HSPs) to stabilize nascent proteins
41 . These TFs in liver showed high connectivity in RES fetuses. Since misfolded proteins are eliminated either by ubiquitination or autophagy
41 , the over-representation of the ubiquitin-mediated proteolysis pathway found here is likely acting in concert with the HSPs. Thus, these evidences suggest that RES fetuses may have shown hepatic cellular stress in response to lipid metabolism imbalances.
